                            <title  key="supplied title">八仙過海圖 卷</title>
                            <author key="_unknown">unknown</author>
                            
                            <note type="注">The "Eight Immortals Crossing the Sea" is a popular theme in Chinese art and literature, depicting a legendary group of eight immortals from Taoist mythology who are said to have crossed the sea together on various magical and whimsical means. </note>
                            <note type="注">The story of the "Eight Immortals Crossing the Sea" is a popular and colorful tale from Chinese mythology. It revolves around a group of eight immortal beings, each possessing unique abilities and attributes, who come together to cross the treacherous Eastern Sea to attend a gathering of the gods. The story is a mix of adventure, magic, and Taoist philosophy.
                                The tale begins with the Eight Immortals receiving an invitation to a divine banquet held by the Queen Mother of the West, a prominent figure in Chinese mythology associated with immortality and longevity. The banquet is to take place on a distant island in the Eastern Sea, and the immortals are excited to attend. For this hand scroll, it depicts a scene of the Eight Immortals using their unique powers and attributes to overcome the obstacles set by the Dragon King and his army.</note>
                            
